{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos304.unitFractionExpressible_zero_right https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos304.unitFractionExpressible_zero_right.","id":"vf_5c8e4b0485f044e3","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #304: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. For integers $1\\leq a<b$ let $N(a,b)$ denote the minimal $k$ such that there exist integers $1<n_1<\\cdots<n_k$ with\\[\\frac{a}{b}=\\frac{1}{n_1}+\\cdots+\\frac{1}{n_k}.\\]Estimate $N(b)=\\max_{1\\leq a<b}N(a,b)$. Is it true that $N(b) \\ll \\log\\log b$? Current best: Erd\\H{o}s \\cite{Er50c} proved that\\[\\log\\log b \\ll N(b) \\ll \\frac{\\log b}{\\log\\log b}.\\]The upper bound was improved by Vose \\cite{Vo85} to\\[N(b) \\ll \\sqrt{\\log b}.\\]One can also investigate the average of $N(a,b)$ for fixed $b$, and it is known that\\[\\frac{1}{b}\\sum_{1\\leq a<b}N(a,b) \\gg \\log\\log b.\\]Related to [18]. Prize: no. OEIS: A097847, A097849. Tags: number theory, unit fractions.","id":"vf_744ba33492744de0","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/304.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_5c8e4b0485f044e3","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:304","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_5c8e4b0485f044e3","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_744ba33492744de0","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":